{{For|individuals with the same or similar name|Abd-ar-Rahman (disambiguation)}}
{{unreferenced|date=October 2008}}

'''Abd ar-Rahman IV Mortada''' ('''عبدالرحمن''') was the [[Caliph of Cordoba]] in the [[Umayyad]] dynasty of the [[Al-Andalus]] ([[Moors|Moorish]] [[Iberian Peninsula|Iberia]]), succeeding [[Suleiman II of Córdoba|Suleiman II]], in 1018. That same year, he was murdered at [[Cadiz]] while fleeing from a battle in which he had been deserted by the very supporters which had brought him into power. His brief reign was similar to that of [[Abd ar-Rahman V|Abd ar-Rahman V Mostadir]].

